cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with machine translation between two languages. Additionally, the use of language models and evaluation metrics further supports this categorization. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses the use of statistical machine translation, which is a subfield of AI and ML. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category as the paper evaluates the effects of data preparation on translation results, which is similar to the process of information retrieval. 

Finally, cs.SD (Software Engineering) could be a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the development, tuning, and testing of the translation system, which involves software engineering principles.
